</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="21.[106,187,1424,1448]" box="[106,187,1424,1448]" pageId="21" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[106,187,1424,1448]" pageId="21" pageNumber="288">Female:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[106,1096,1462,1640]" lastBlockId="22.[189,1180,175,536]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="289" pageId="21" pageNumber="288">
Length, 
<quantity box="[192,277,1462,1486]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="288" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
; forewing length 
<quantity box="[453,538,1462,1486]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="288" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
; ovipositor length, 
<quantity box="[734,819,1462,1486]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="288" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[828,883,1462,1486]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="288">Color</emphasis>
: Antenna black with scape and pedicel orange. Head and mesonotum orange, rest of mesosoma black; fore- and midleg coxae, trochanters, and femora black, tibiae and tarsi white; hind leg black with basal quarter of tibia and all tarsus white. Metasoma black with white band on second segment. Ovipositor sheath with white band. Wings hyaline, veins and stigma black; forewing with faint black spot under stigma and spot at apex black. 
<emphasis box="[488,541,1616,1640]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="288">Head</emphasis>
: Antennal length 2.5X head width. Lower interocular distance subequal to eye height; malar space 0.25X eye height (
<figureCitation box="[822,899,175,199]" captionStart="Figs 30-33" captionStartId="21.[106,144,1376,1398]" captionTargetBox="[115,1090,174,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-110@21.[115,1090,174,1368]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 30-33: Aulacus leon. 30Xead, front. 31Xead, dorsal. 32 Mesosoma, lateral. 33 Mesosoma dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5364496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5364496/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="289">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). From above, head straight behind eyes then roundly narrowing, head behind eyes about 0.7X eye length (
<figureCitation box="[1004,1079,206,230]" captionStart="Figs 30-33" captionStartId="21.[106,144,1376,1398]" captionTargetBox="[115,1090,174,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-110@21.[115,1090,174,1368]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 30-33: Aulacus leon. 30Xead, front. 31Xead, dorsal. 32 Mesosoma, lateral. 33 Mesosoma dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5364496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5364496/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="289">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Shining with fine white pubescence; gena and vertex with large punctures, interspaces mostly 2 or more times puncture diameters; frons evenly punctate with flat shining interspaces mostly about equal to puncture diameters (
<figureCitation box="[449,574,298,322]" captionStart="Figs 30-33" captionStartId="21.[106,144,1376,1398]" captionTargetBox="[115,1090,174,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-110@21.[115,1090,174,1368]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 30-33: Aulacus leon. 30Xead, front. 31Xead, dorsal. 32 Mesosoma, lateral. 33 Mesosoma dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5364496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5364496/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="289">Figs 30, 31</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority=": Propleuron" authorityName="Propleuron" box="[600,834,298,322]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="22" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[600,699,298,321]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="289">Mesosoma</emphasis>
: Propleuron
</taxonomicName>
shining, punctate. Mesonotum with rather evenly reticulate sculpture, that on mesoscutum somewhat transverse; notauli meet posteriorly at point of transscutal articulation (
<figureCitation box="[669,746,359,383]" captionStart="Figs 30-33" captionStartId="21.[106,144,1376,1398]" captionTargetBox="[115,1090,174,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-110@21.[115,1090,174,1368]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 30-33: Aulacus leon. 30Xead, front. 31Xead, dorsal. 32 Mesosoma, lateral. 33 Mesosoma dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5364496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5364496/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="289">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
). Pronotum coarsely reticulate posteriorly, anteriorly reticulations finer; mesopleuron, metapleuron, and propodeum reticulate, with area of fine punctures on upper central part of mesopleuron (
<figureCitation box="[748,868,420,444]" captionStart="Figs 30-33" captionStartId="21.[106,144,1376,1398]" captionTargetBox="[115,1090,174,1365]" captionTargetId="figure-110@21.[115,1090,174,1368]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 30-33: Aulacus leon. 30Xead, front. 31Xead, dorsal. 32 Mesosoma, lateral. 33 Mesosoma dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5364496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5364496/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="289">Figs 32, 33</figureCitation>
). Hind basitarsus 1.2X longer than length of remaining tarsal segments combined. Hind coxa shining above, finely punctate to striate and duller laterally, about 2.0X longer than broad. 
<emphasis box="[772,873,482,505]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="289">Metasoma</emphasis>
: Segments 2 or 3 to apex with fine white pubescence and fine punctures. Ovipositor length subequal to forewing length.
</paragraph>
