</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="289" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,287,782,806]" box="[189,287,782,806]" pageId="22" pageNumber="289">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,287,782,806]" pageId="22" pageNumber="289">Remarks:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[189,1179,820,936]" pageId="22" pageNumber="289">
This species and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Townes" authorityYear="1950" box="[361,456,820,844]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Aulacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispilis">
<emphasis box="[361,456,820,844]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="289">A. dispilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="2008" box="[607,676,820,844]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Aulacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leon">
<emphasis box="[607,676,820,844]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="289">A. leon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the ovipositor length is subequal to the forewing length, the ovipositor sheath has a white band, and the propodeum is black. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Townes" authorityYear="1950" box="[1033,1131,851,875]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Aulacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispilis">
<emphasis box="[1033,1131,851,875]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="289">A. dispilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the ovipositor length is longer than the forewing length, the ovipositor sheath is black, and the mesosoma is orange with black, if present, confined to the lower portion of the pleura.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
